dataIdInfo.idPurp:
This layer is intended for reference and mapping purposes, and may be used for basic applications such as viewing, querying, and map output production, or to provide a basemap to support graphical overlays and analysis with other spatial data.
[This file contains the zoning polygons for all parcels in Jefferson County. The data is complete for all the Towns. We are in the process of collecting data for all Cities and Villages and adding that data to this file. As of Oct. 2010, we had data for the Cities of Watertown, Fort Atkinson, Lake Mills & Waterloo and for the Villages of Johnson Creek and Palmyra.]
dataIdInfo.idAbs: This polygon data layer represents zoning for Jefferson County, Wisconsin in 2017. It is a feature class within the geodatabase, Jefferson_Zoning_2017.gdb.[This file contains the polygons for all parcels in Jefferson County and the data related to the zone of the parcel.]

This data was submitted to the UW geospatial archive in 2018. Content may be considered current as of December 31, 2017. It was published to the UW geospatial archive as part of the Wisconsin Department of Administration Land Information Program annual collection of public data for the year 2018.
